  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      -  Objective: To compare clinical results of three types of manual tooth brushes on
           gingivitis and plaque removal efficacy.

        -  Material and Methods: This study is a single blind randomized trial with crossover
           design which involved 30 periodontally healthy individuals. At baseline professional
           plaque removal and oral hygiene instruction are performed for all the students, then
           they are asked to avoid brushing for 1-2 days. Thereafter plaque and gingivitis scores
           are measured using plaque and gingival indices (PI and GI). Then subjects are instructed
           to use Pulsar tooth brush for a two-week period and then, GI and PI indices are assessed
           again. After passing one-week period for wash out, subjects don't brush for 1-2 days and
           indices are recorded again. The same procedure are done for Cross action, and Butler 411
           tooth brushes respectively.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
